1904-Rules:
1905:- Create requires `credit.appraisal.create`, `credit.risk_assessment.manage`, and the existing
1906-  application object-access boundary. It requires a stored eligibility projection with
1907-  `overall_result = eligible` and a stored loan-limit projection; missing or non-eligible facts
1908:  return `409 INVALID_STATE_TRANSITION` without appraisal, risk, audit, or workflow rows.
1909:- One appraisal and one linked risk assessment are stored per loan application. Create copies the
1910-  exact canonical redacted projections returned by `EligibilityAssessmentModule` and
1911-  `LoanLimitCalculator`, plus their UUID provenance. GET, PATCH amount/exception validation,
1912:  submit, review, and sanction consumers use those appraisal-owned frozen projections; a later
1913:  successful same-UUID assessment rerun cannot reinterpret the appraisal.
1914-- Required summaries and `repayment_capacity_notes` are non-blank. Recommended amount is positive; optional tenure is a positive
1915-  integer; supplied interest type is `floating`; recommendation is `approve`, `reject`, or
1916-  `conditions`; all four risk ratings are `low`, `medium`, or `high`. Unknown top-level or nested
1917-  fields return `400 VALIDATION_ERROR`.
1918-- A recommendation above the frozen final eligible amount is rejected unless that frozen
1919-  loan-limit projection already has `exception_required_flag = true`; this contract does not create an
1920-  exception approval.
1921:- PATCH is draft-only and changes supplied fields only. It requires `credit.appraisal.update`;
1922-  changing nested risk fields additionally requires `credit.risk_assessment.manage`.
1923-- GET is side-effect free and is allowed to scoped holders of create/update/submit-review or the
1924-  Credit Manager review permission. Missing notes return `404 NOT_FOUND`.
1925-- `tat_due_at` is application `created_at + 2 days` and never resets. At the exact due instant TAT
1926-  is `within_tat`; later preparation/submission is `breached`.
1927:- Submit requires `credit.appraisal.submit_review`, object scope, and non-blank `remarks`; it
1928:  persists trimmed remarks on the appraisal and atomically transitions `draft -> review_pending`
1929-  once. Submit additionally requires `prerequisite_provenance = verified`; repeated submit and
1930-  later PATCH return `409 INVALID_STATE_TRANSITION`.
1931:- The revalidation action accepts only `{}`, requires `credit.appraisal.update` plus
1932-  `credit.risk_assessment.manage`, object scope, and `draft` state, and replaces only prerequisite
1933-  IDs/projections/provenance with the current public eligible projections. It never changes
1934-  recommendation, repayment, risk, summary, TAT, or preparer facts. Legacy rows whose chronology
1935-  cannot prove their mutable assessments were the original inputs remain `legacy_unverified` until
1936-  this explicit action succeeds.
1937:- Create/update/submit write `appraisal.created`, `appraisal.updated`, or
1938:  `appraisal.submitted_for_review` metadata-only audit/workflow evidence. Free-text summaries,
1939-  mitigation notes, repayment-capacity notes, and submit remarks are never copied into evidence
1940:  JSON. Submit audit metadata records only `submission_reason_exists` and its appraisal owner ID;
1941-  revalidation metadata records projection UUIDs and provenance only.
1942-- Review always requires `decision` and non-blank `review_comments`; `decision` is `reviewed`,
1943-  `returned`, or `rejected`. `reviewed` and `returned` continue to accept exactly those two fields.
1944-  `rejected` additionally requires the existing 005H rejection-note fields
1945-  `rejection_reason_category`, non-blank `detailed_reason`, boolean `reapply_allowed_flag`, and
1946-  `communication_mode`; the workflow fixes `rejection_stage = credit_assessment`. Missing, invalid,
1947-  blank, or unknown fields return `400 VALIDATION_ERROR` without success evidence.
1948:- Every review decision requires `credit.appraisal.review`, Credit Manager credit-domain object
1949-  access, `review_pending` state, `prerequisite_provenance = verified`, and a reviewer other than
1950-  the preparer. Create/update/submit-review permissions do not imply rejection authority. Missing
1951-  permission and object scope return their existing distinct `403` codes.
1952:- `reviewed` transitions to terminal appraisal state `reviewed`. `returned` records the same
1953-  reviewer/time/comment/decision facts and transitions to `draft`, where the maker must revise and
1954-  resubmit before another review. Draft, reviewed, repeated, and other non-pending review attempts
1955-  return `409 INVALID_STATE_TRANSITION`.
1956:- `rejected` atomically transitions to terminal appraisal state `rejected` and creates exactly one
1957-  linked existing 005H rejection-note draft. Its response nests the serialized `rejection_note`,
1958-  including `note_status = draft`, derived `communication_status = not_sent`, null send facts, and
1959:  the appraisal/application/note IDs. It does not send communication or create a sanction/approval
1960-  case. Repeated rejection returns `409` and cannot create a duplicate note.
1961:- Review never reads current eligibility or loan-limit rows. It preserves the appraisal-owned
1962-  projections, recommendation/terms, repayment-capacity and submission reasons, linked risk, and
1963:  TAT facts. Successful decisions atomically write `appraisal.reviewed` or `appraisal.returned`
1964-  audit/workflow evidence containing only IDs, state, decision, actor/time, and request ID; free
1965:  text review comments and appraisal/risk projections are excluded.
1966:- Rejected review uses the same outer transaction for appraisal state, rejection-note persistence,
