 | A-056 | Ambiguous legacy appraisal repair uses `POST /api/v1/appraisal-notes/{id}/revalidate-prerequisites/` with an empty body, appraisal-update plus risk-management permission, object scope, and draft-only state. | ADR-0003 and 006E2 require explicit authorised revalidation but the source API document does not name its path/body. A dedicated action endpoint matches API §3, avoids overloading PATCH, and changes only frozen prerequisite facts. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §3/§24; `docs/adr/ADR-0003-freeze-appraisal-prerequisite-projections.md`; `docs/slices/006E2-appraisal-source-contract-and-snapshot-hardening.md` | 006E2 and later appraisal review/sanction slices | High | Yes | 2026-07-10 | If governance names a different repair action, version/alias the route while retaining draft-only authorisation, immutable caller-authored facts, and metadata-only evidence. |
 | A-057 | A rejected Credit Manager review extends the §24.4 request with top-level `rejection_reason_category`, `detailed_reason`, `reapply_allowed_flag`, and `communication_mode`; `rejection_stage` is fixed by the workflow to `credit_assessment`. These extra fields are required only for `decision = rejected`, while `reviewed` and `returned` continue to accept exactly `decision` and `review_comments`. | M04-FR-011 requires the review action to generate the existing rejection note, but §24.4 names only decision/comments while §21.3 and data-model §13.6 require category, detailed reason, reapply flag, and communication mode. Requiring the source fields avoids inventing defaults; fixing the stage is an invariant of the appraisal workflow rather than caller choice. | `docs/source/functional-spec.md` M04-FR-011; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §21.3/§24.4; `docs/source/data-model.md` §13.6; `docs/slices/006F2-credit-manager-appraisal-rejection.md` | 006F2 and later rejection/sanction slices | High | Yes | 2026-07-10 | If source governance defines a nested request or different review fields, version the adapter while retaining the public appraisal/rejection-note module seams and existing stored note contract. |
